cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about a novel architecture for real-time semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new feature fusion module, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to balance speed and segmentation performance, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several datasets, which could also place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
